a2228 9
 *	The test for errno not equal to EPERM is to work around a
 *	bug in SunOS for the Sun-4, where bru was issuing a spurious
 *	warning message because the close was getting a bogus error
 *	return (with errno set to EPERM).  This does somewhat reduce
 *	the effectiveness of checking for an error return in the first
 *	place.  But considering that most other programs don't even
 *	bother, we still come out ahead on brownie points.  We could
 *	uglify the code by ifdef'ing it, but it hardly seems worth
 *	the bother.
